The paper discusses the use of prior knowledge in the form of a causal graph to guide model selection and improve model robustness. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it deals with improving the performance of machine learning models. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of Structural Causal Models (SCMs) and likelihood calculations, which are commonly used in the fields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computational Engineering (cs.CE). The paper also deals with datasets and domains, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
